metadata.name: INCAPTIVITY #2
metadata.description: INCAPTIVITY is a collection of artworks created from human suffering while experiencing incarceration.  The collection is very broad from imaginary thoughts of the mind through tears of joy and pain on to the simplest thing of what one can and cannot touch with the human hand. Part of the INCAPTIVITY series titled “Hands of Time” is currently on display at the Palm Springs Art Museum.
